request.description:
A shipment can be updated by making a PATCH call. The required field is the shipment ID. All the other fields are optional and it is advised to only send the fields that changed to the endpoint. The example includes all the fields that can possibly be updated.

To update a shipment status (and create a tracking event) send e.g.

```
{
  "tracking_reference": "SND123456789",
  "status": "delivered",
}

 ```

Instead of passing the `tracking_reference` (of the shipment, not the individual parcel), the shipment `id` can also be used instead.

To set the time of a status change, for example to `delivered`, also pass `time_modified` through (set to the time of the respective event). The format of date fields are `2021-02-02T13:22:05.476831Z` (UTC time).

To add a message or other details to the tracking event, e.g. `Picked up from the kiosk` when updating the shipment's status to `collected`, send through the `metadata` field. All metadata fields are optional. The `message` and `location` fields are visible on the public tracking page. All other fields are only visible on the client and admin portal when viewing the tracking events for the shipment. The `data` field can contain any arbitrary data fields that will also be added to the tracking event.

```
{
  "tracking_reference": "SND123456789",
  "status": "collected",
  "time_modified": "2021-02-02T13:22:05.476831Z",
  "metadata": {
    "tracking_info": {
      "message": "Picked up from the kiosk",
      "lat": -25.806655,
      "lng": 28.334732,
      "location": "Johannesburg",
      "bay": "Quick collect",
      "data": {
        "kiosk_terminal": 3,
        "kiosk_attendant": "Jane Doe"
      }
    }
  }
}

 ```

Please note that updating a shipment's `addresses`, `parcels`, opt-in rates or service level might have an affect on the rate charged.
